# if period != 0 --> round to three decimal places and convert to string
# check if period is amongst specified periods, if not then interpolate coefficients linearly in log log



# I can make this class implement the __call__ method wherein I could call it as 
# a function which returns the dict of coefficients; the difference would be that
# the calls to the function need to be made using () whereas the openquake code
# uses []; hence, the [] would have to be changed to function calls

#%% Make a class for the CoeffsTable

